abstract: BALTIMORE, Jan. 3 -- Just as the great clock of the cathedral struck the hour of 11 to-day the head of a long line of seminarians emerged from the sacristy. abstract: TOPEKA, Kan., Jan. 17. -- Judge Theodosius Botkin arrived here direct from his home in Seward County early yesterday morning. After resting several hours at the hotel he called upon Gov. abstract: SAN ANTONIO, Texas, Jan. 20. -- The whole of the Rio Grande frontier is covered with snow for the first time ever known. The suffering among the poorer classes of Mexicans and among the United States troops has been intense for the last two days. The Mexicans prefer war and pestilence to cold weather, and the activity of the wily revolutionists who were in the range of the blizzard has been visibly suppressed.

Stanley, will probably not arrive for several days.
